(43, 6, 53, 66, 2, 17, 17, 'ye have no life in you', 'Connection of Life and Manna', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sustenance through divine means. In John, eating the flesh and drinking the blood of Jesus signifies spiritual life, while Revelation speaks of hidden manna as a reward for the faithful, suggesting a connection between spiritual nourishment and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 53, 40, 18, 3, 3, 'ye have no life in you', 'Connection of Life and Conversion', 'This connection highlights the necessity of transformation for spiritual life. Both passages emphasize the requirement of a specific action—eating and drinking in John, and becoming as little children in Matthew—to attain life and enter the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
